I had none. I was trying to choose ones that seemed likely as true. I was hoping my clues in the beginning were true and I based it off that.
I just went with what seemed right, I went by intuition.

I tried to evaluate clues as they came, but more importantly, I looked at clues as a whole to see what fit together and what didn't make sense. I occasionally changed categories of clues/dead ends as more information was revealed.
find clue that make sense
Just played
I only picked leads that two or more collaborators said they had seen the same thing. Not the ones that only one collaborator had.
I tried to group clues that made sense
Look at each clue and see if there were any others that matched it at all.
I just used my best guess
collect and analyze information
I didn't have much of a strategy. I just read the clues and tried to determine was was relevant.
I tried to pair likely scenarios together.  I got confused a bit.

Look for clues that seemed more like evidence. At first I wasn't worrying as much about putting in dead end answers because they don't affect the bonus. But then it seemed like I would get more clues if I removed some. Not sure.
Gut instinct, I couldn't remember all the details on the previous page.
The more items pointing to a culprit the better
I started grouping evidence first then started forming a decision based on clues that tied back to the direct evidence.
to win
I looked for the most concrete evidence then worked my way out.
good
I kept an open mind about the validity of clues and tried to weed the less relevant ones out
reading the clues and seeing what others were choosing and thinking what seemed most reasonable from the clues
I tried to follow the leads.
i went with what clues linked to other clues
eliminate information that wasn't relevant
I read the clues and kept the ones I was sure were right under promising leads.  As more clues came in I weighed them against what I already knew
Try to build a profile of the burglar using one person (the one with the most clues) as a suspect and discarding all the other information for all other suspects.
Payed attention to what clues others selected and my instinct
I tried to reason what made the most sense based on the clues.
I read all the clues I had, and then I read all the clues my partners had.
Trying to connect the dots the best way possible.
multiple eye witness report was bound to be true
I guess thinking about what might make sense, plus how many of us agreed upon the different clues.
I looked for motive and opportunity.

My strategy was to look for things that were definite and then try to piece together the unknown items
